<relation name="Domain" id="domain" type="both" inverse="hasdomain" n="true" v="true" a="true" r="true" s="true">

  <img src="domain.png"/>

  <description>
    <span>Domain of synset.</span>
    <!-- @formatter:off -->
    <ul>
      <li>A concept which is a Topic, Region or Usage pointer of a given concept.</li>
      <li>A concept which is the scientific category pointer of a given concept.</li>
      <li>A concept which is a geographical / cultural domain pointer of a given concept.</li>
      <li>A concept which is the type of a given concept.</li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Domain</b> is an underspecified relation between two concepts where Concept B is a Topic (scientific category), Region or Usage pointer of Concept A.</li>
      <li><b>Domain Topic</b> is a relation between two concepts where Concept B is a <i>scientific category</i> (e.g. computing, sport, biology, etc.) of concept A.</li>
      <li><b>Domain Region</b> is a relation between two concepts where Concept B is a <i>geographical / cultural</i> domain of concept A.</li>
      <li><b>Is Exemplified By</b> is a relation between two concepts where Concept B is a type of Concept A, such as idiom, honorific or classifier. The name was changed from "Domain - USAGE".</li>
    </ul>
    <!-- @formatter:on -->
  </description>

  <phrases>
    <phrase>
